headline.main: France Drops Electronic Voting for Citizens Abroad Over Cybersecurity Fears
headline.print_headline: France Drops Electronic Voting for Citizens Abroad Over Cybersecurity Fears

lead_paragraph: France's government has dropped plans to let its citizens abroad vote electronically in legislative elections in June because of concern about the risk of cyber attacks, the Foreign Ministry said on Monday.
